RESIDENTIAL LEASE AGREEMENT

Hollywood Heights Apartments
Apex Property Management LLC
1247 Vine Street, Los Angeles, California 90028

LEASE AGREEMENT entered into this 1st day of March, 2026.

LANDLORD: Apex Property Management LLC, a California limited liability company ("Landlord")
TENANT: [Tenant Name] ("Tenant")
PREMISES: Unit 4B, 1247 Vine Street, Los Angeles, California 90028 ("Premises")

1. TERM
This Lease shall commence on March 1, 2026 and continue for a period of twelve (12) months, terminating on February 28, 2027. Following the initial term, this Lease shall automatically renew on a month-to-month basis unless either party provides written notice of termination no less than ninety (90) days prior to the desired termination date.

2. RENT
Tenant agrees to pay Landlord the sum of THREE THOUSAND TWO HUNDRED DOLLARS ($3,200.00) per month as rent for the Premises. Rent is due on the first (1st) day of each calendar month. Rent shall be payable to Apex Property Management LLC at the address set forth above or at such other place as Landlord may from time to time designate.

3. SECURITY DEPOSIT
Upon execution of this Lease, Tenant shall deposit with Landlord the sum of NINE THOUSAND SIX HUNDRED DOLLARS ($9,600.00) as a security deposit ("Security Deposit"). The Security Deposit shall be held by Landlord as security for Tenant's faithful performance of all terms, covenants, and conditions of this Lease. The Security Deposit is not to be used as last month's rent. Landlord reserves the right to apply the Security Deposit to any unpaid rent, damages, cleaning costs, or other charges owed by Tenant.

4. LATE CHARGES
If Tenant fails to pay rent within five (5) days after the due date, Tenant agrees to pay a late charge as determined by Landlord in its sole discretion. Tenant acknowledges that such late charge represents a fair and reasonable estimate of costs incurred by Landlord as a result of such late payment and agrees to pay such additional rent.

5. ENTRY BY LANDLORD
Landlord and its agents shall have the right to enter the Premises at any time for any purpose including but not limited to: inspection, repairs, improvements, showing the Premises to prospective tenants or buyers, or any other lawful purpose. Landlord shall provide reasonable notice prior to entry when practicable, but no specific notice period is guaranteed.

6. UTILITIES
Tenant shall be responsible for payment of all utilities and services for the Premises, including electricity, gas, water, sewer, trash, internet, and telephone.

7. PETS
Pets are permitted with prior written approval from Landlord. A non-refundable pet fee of FIVE HUNDRED DOLLARS ($500.00) per pet is required. Landlord may revoke permission for pets at any time if Tenant fails to comply with pet policies.

8. REPAIRS AND MAINTENANCE
Tenant shall maintain the Premises in a clean and sanitary condition and shall not permit any damage to occur. Tenant shall be responsible for all repairs necessitated by Tenant's negligence or misuse, including repairs to appliances, fixtures, and all components of the Premises. Tenant expressly waives any right to repair the Premises and deduct costs from rent.

9. ALTERATIONS
Tenant shall make no alterations, additions, or improvements to the Premises without prior written consent of Landlord. All approved alterations shall become the property of Landlord unless Landlord requests removal in writing.

10. ASSIGNMENT AND SUBLETTING
Tenant shall not assign this Lease or sublet the Premises or any part thereof without the prior written consent of Landlord. Landlord may withhold consent for any reason or no reason at all.

11. TERMINATION
In the event Tenant vacates or abandons the Premises, Landlord shall have the right to re-enter and re-let the Premises without notice and without terminating this Lease. Landlord may re-enter and take possession of the Premises in the event of any default by Tenant without resort to judicial proceedings if Landlord determines in its sole discretion that the Premises have been abandoned or vacated.

12. DEFAULT
If Tenant defaults in payment of rent or in the performance of any other term of this Lease, Landlord may, at its option, terminate this Lease by serving Tenant with written notice. In the event of default, Landlord shall be entitled to recover all past due rent, future rent for the balance of the lease term, costs of re-letting, and all attorney's fees and costs incurred in enforcing this Lease.

13. ATTORNEY'S FEES
In the event of any legal action or proceeding arising out of this Lease, Landlord shall be entitled to recover reasonable attorney's fees and costs from Tenant if Landlord prevails. Tenant shall not be entitled to attorney's fees in any such proceeding.

14. INDEMNIFICATION
Tenant agrees to indemnify and hold harmless Landlord from any and all claims, damages, losses, or expenses, including attorney's fees, arising from Tenant's use of the Premises or any act or omission of Tenant, whether or not such claims arise from Tenant's negligence.

15. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY
Landlord shall not be liable for any damage to Tenant's property arising from any cause, including but not limited to theft, fire, water leakage, or the acts or negligence of other tenants or third parties. Tenant expressly waives all claims for damages against Landlord arising from any such cause.

16. JURY TRIAL WAIVER
TENANT AND LANDLORD HEREBY WAIVE THE RIGHT TO A JURY TRIAL in any action, proceeding, or counterclaim arising out of or in connection with this Lease or the use or occupancy of the Premises.

17. RENT INCREASES
Landlord reserves the right to increase rent upon thirty (30) days written notice to Tenant. Tenant's continued occupancy after such notice shall constitute acceptance of the new rental rate.

18. RULES AND REGULATIONS
Tenant agrees to comply with all rules and regulations established by Landlord, as amended from time to time in Landlord's sole discretion, without prior notice to Tenant.

19. NOISE AND NUISANCE
Tenant shall not create, maintain, or permit any nuisance, noise, or disturbance that interferes with the quiet enjoyment of other tenants or neighbors. Violations may result in immediate termination at Landlord's discretion.

20. ENTIRE AGREEMENT
This Lease constitutes the entire agreement between the parties. No modification shall be binding unless in writing and signed by Landlord. Landlord may modify the rules and regulations attached hereto at any time without Tenant's consent.

LANDLORD: Apex Property Management LLC
By: _________________________ Date: ___________

TENANT: _________________________ Date: ___________
